DIGEST
SB 236 Reengrossed 2026 Regular Session Owen
Proposed law provides legislative intent relative to the importance of prevention, early
screening, diagnosis, and treatment of kidney disease.
Proposed law requires the La. Dept. of Health to conduct an annual review of all medications
and forms of treatment for chronic and rare kidney diseases and services for enrollees with
a diagnosis of chronic or rare kidney disease that are eligible for coverage under Medicaid.
Proposed law requires the department to examine and pursue strategic partnerships with
state-based entities who represent or provide services to individuals living with chronic and
rare kidney diseases for the purpose of increasing education, awareness, and diagnostic
screening for chronic and rare kidney diseases.
Proposed law requires the department to submit an annual report to the Senate president, the
speaker of the House, and the committees on health and welfare beginning July 1, 2027, that
details the department's findings from the annual review and any recommendations to the
legislature.
Effective August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 46:450.5.1)
